- Come on, Vince.

01:40.851 --> 01:43.978
I'm serious.
I'm absolutely in love with this woman.

01:44.062 --> 01:45.938
What? Was the sex that good?

01:46.023 --> 01:47.940
Well, yeah, but that's not it.

01:48.025 --> 01:49.984
It's that or you're back on drugs.

01:50.068 --> 01:51.569
I'm clearer than I've ever been.

01:51.653 --> 01:53.279
Well, did you drug her?

01:53.363 --> 01:58.326
No. Guys, I tried telling you
the moment I met her, this is it.

01:58.410 --> 02:00.077
I thought you guys helped me
'cause you believed.

02:00.162 --> 02:03.831
We believe, Vince. It's just taping
your exes' testimonies to marriage

02:03.916 --> 02:06.459
is a pretty big leap.
We need a little time to adjust.

02:06.543 --> 02:09.419
No time. We're going to Paris tonight
and I want you all at the ceremony.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.964
Are you sure you didn't take any drugs, bro?

02:12.049 --> 02:14.801
I'm clean and sober. I'm 1 00% sure about this.

02:15.636 --> 02:17.386
- Then we're in.
- Good.

02:17.471 --> 02:19.931
Now let's hear you top that news.

02:21.266 --> 02:22.725
Sloan's pregnant.

02:25.229 --> 02:27.104
- Ari?
- What?

02:27.189 --> 02:29.023
- Ari!
- What is it?

02:29.107 --> 02:31.818
Your football coaches are here.

02:31.902 --> 02:33.903
- What?
- The ones you paid a fortune to come

02:33.987 --> 02:38.157
- and motivate your troops.
- Right, right, right.

02:38.242 --> 02:41.160
Send them to the troops.
I don't need motivation.

02:41.245 --> 02:43.120
Actually, you do.

02:43.205 --> 02:45.915
And you went against my vote on this,
so please just get up

02:46.041 --> 02:48.501
- and at least say hello.
- Okay.

02:50.254 --> 02:51.754
And try to present some strength.

02:51.839 --> 02:55.508
They can potentially bring in some very big
clients for our sports department.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.302
Do I not look strong?

02:59.471 --> 03:02.223
There they are! Barry. How are you, guys?

03:02.307 --> 03:03.516
- Mike.
- What's up, Ari?

03:03.600 --> 03:04.767
- All right.
- How are you doing, Ari?

03:04.852 --> 03:07.186
- How are you doing?
- How do I look?

03:07.271 --> 03:09.772
- You look like shit. You been eating?
- I have not been.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.190
- Everything all right?
- He's fine.

03:11.275 --> 03:14.026
Well, I'm getting divorced, actually.

03:14.111 --> 03:15.695
- Sorry to hear about that, Ari.
- Yeah, that's tough.

03:15.779 --> 03:17.780
- Yeah, it is.
- Gentlemen, he's fine.

03:17.865 --> 03:21.075
Well, actually, I'm devastated.

03:21.535 --> 03:24.579
Yeah, but I don't...
I don't wanna bring your energy down.

03:24.663 --> 03:27.915
Go and tell my people
what it's like to control 350-Ib men

03:28.000 --> 03:29.709
who are usually carrying firearms, okay?

03:29.960 --> 03:31.711
Motivate my losers!

03:35.299 --> 03:37.216
I gotta go.

03:37.301 --> 03:38.801
- He's a fucking mess.
- He is.

03:39.553 --> 03:41.721
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:43.140 --> 03:46.976
- What are you doing here?
- I needed to talk.

03:47.060 --> 03:49.854
- You all right?
- Well, I haven't been sleeping.

03:49.938 --> 03:52.064
Me either. Or eating.

03:52.149 --> 03:54.650
We need to tell
the kids what's going on.

03:54.735 --> 03:57.111
This is hanging over everything.

03:57.195 --> 03:58.863
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:00.324 --> 04:05.036
And I was wondering
if you wanted to do that together.

04:05.954 --> 04:09.248
Oh, yeah, we should...
We should do that together.

04:09.333 --> 04:12.460
Okay. I think we should go to Dr. Marcus
and ask for her advice.

04:13.170 --> 04:14.545
Why do we need her advice?

04:14.630 --> 04:16.797
I need it and I'd like you to be there.

04:17.132 --> 04:18.716
Sure.

04:18.800 --> 04:21.844
Can you do it today? She's available at 1:00.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.262
Okay.

04:23.847 --> 04:25.056
Thanks.

04:26.683 --> 04:28.601
I don't understand.
What are you gonna do in New York?

04:28.685 --> 04:31.187
- I'll figure it out.
- And you're just gonna throw everything away

04:31.271 --> 04:32.438
that you built here the last eight years?

04:32.522 --> 04:34.982
- Yeah. What choice do I have?
- Convince Sloan to stay.

04:35.067 --> 04:37.318
Oh, come on, Vince.
You don't think I tried that?

04:37.402 --> 04:39.111
She won't pick up the phone.

04:39.196 --> 04:41.656
I mean, I spoke to her lawyer.
I can't force her to stay.

04:41.740 --> 04:43.616
I can't even prove I'm the father
till the baby is born.

04:43.700 --> 04:46.619
- I have no rights.
- I'm sure it's not gonna come to that.

04:46.703 --> 04:50.206
Yeah. I know you guys always make fun of me
'cause I'm a good conservative Catholic boy,

04:50.290 --> 04:52.875
but this isn't exactly the way I drew things up
if you know what I mean.

04:52.960 --> 04:55.962
- Now you're gonna have to adjust.
- To what?

04:56.046 --> 04:58.547
The only thing I can do
is go to New York and do my best

04:58.632 --> 05:01.133
to be as big a part of this kid's life as I can be.

05:01.218 --> 05:03.803
Were you even gonna tell me about this?

05:03.887 --> 05:07.807
- I called you last night.
- Yeah. Sorry, I was with Sophia.

05:07.891 --> 05:10.559
- Yeah. How was that?
- Amazing.

05:10.894 --> 05:12.436
- That's great.
- Really great.

05:12.521 --> 05:15.314
- In fact, I need to ask you something.
- What?

05:15.399 --> 05:18.401
- Will you come to Paris with us tonight?
- With you and Sophia?

05:18.485 --> 05:21.570
And Turtle and Johnny
and of course I wanna invite Ari.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.406
- Invite him to what?
- To my wedding.

05:26.576 --> 05:30.037
Vince, in all honesty, I don't have time
for this shit right now. Please.

05:30.122 --> 05:33.207
E, I'm serious. I want you to be my best man.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.251
- Jesus Christ.
- Hey!

05:35.335 --> 05:37.253
- Why don't I talk to Sloan?
- What? No!

05:37.337 --> 05:39.630
- I think she'll listen to me.
- No, you listen to me!

05:39.756 --> 05:42.133
I don't want you getting involved, all right?

05:42.217 --> 05:43.759
Sloan's family hates me enough as it is.

05:43.844 --> 05:45.302
The only thing you're gonna do
is make it worse.

05:45.387 --> 05:46.679
How can I make it worse?

05:46.763 --> 05:49.432
Well, I don't know. But a guy who's getting
married to a girl after 24 hours

05:49.516 --> 05:51.183
probably isn't the best guy
to take advice from.

05:51.268 --> 05:53.227
Yeah, maybe you're right. But either way,

05:54.438 --> 05:57.648
come to Paris just for a few days.

05:57.733 --> 05:59.650
I couldn't do this without you.

06:03.113 --> 06:04.280
Hello?

06:05.449 --> 06:06.532
Oh, hey, Sloan.

06:06.742 --> 06:09.869
I should have expected
E would send the gang over.

06:09.953 --> 06:12.788
- E has no idea we're here.
- We're actually here for Vince.

06:12.873 --> 06:15.541
- What's the difference?
Sloan, we know you're upset.

06:15.625 --> 06:17.960
We understand, but Vince is getting married.

06:18.587 --> 06:19.712
And he wants you to come to the wedding.

06:19.796 --> 06:23.090
Guys, I appreciate the effort,
but I'm not gonna fall for this.

06:23.633 --> 06:25.468
No, no. Sloan, this is no joke.

06:25.552 --> 06:27.094
He really is getting married.

06:27.179 --> 06:29.889
To who? He was single last Wednesday.

06:29.973 --> 06:32.933
Her name is Sophia Lear
and she's our second-favorite woman,

06:33.018 --> 06:35.728
after you, of course. But she's amazing

06:36.021 --> 06:38.147
and they are in love.

06:38.231 --> 06:41.192
Look, this is gonna be
a very exclusive affair,

06:41.276 --> 06:43.069
but it's important to Vince that you attend.

06:43.153 --> 06:44.403
It's important to all of us.

06:45.197 --> 06:47.948
And why am I such an important guest?

06:48.366 --> 06:49.867
'Cause you're carrying our baby.

06:49.993 --> 06:53.079
- Your baby?
Yeah. That's the way we are, Sloan.

06:53.163 --> 06:56.332
You know that. Even if you lose E,
you're never gonna lose us.

06:58.126 --> 07:00.544
- When is it?
- Tonight.

07:01.129 --> 07:02.797
You guys are messing with me.

07:03.173 --> 07:08.511
No, no, Sloan, Vince is getting married,
and we want you to be there.

07:09.888 --> 07:11.806
Where is it?

07:11.890 --> 07:15.476
- Paris.
- This isn't even a good trick!

07:15.769 --> 07:18.771
What? You wanna get me
on a plane to Paris with E and you think

07:18.855 --> 07:21.065
that's gonna make me
forget all that's happened?

07:21.149 --> 07:22.942
No, Sloan.
We want you at the wedding.

07:23.026 --> 07:26.862
I swear on my life
that Vince is going to Paris to get married.

07:26.947 --> 07:31.700
And it's really important to him and to us
that you and your little baby

07:31.785 --> 07:35.538
- are present.
- I appreciate that.

07:36.373 --> 07:38.541
So you'll come?

07:39.876 --> 07:43.087
I have to ask you something else
and I need you to be honest.

07:43.171 --> 07:45.131
Yeah! I swear on my life.

07:45.215 --> 07:47.007
Swear on your career.

07:48.802 --> 07:49.885
Okay.

07:51.555 --> 07:52.888
Did E fuck Melinda?

07:52.973 --> 07:55.766
No, no. I swear on my career

07:55.892 --> 07:57.768
E did not fuck Melinda.

08:02.858 --> 08:05.151
What time does the plane leave?

08:05.235 --> 08:06.485
8:00 p. m.

08:07.904 --> 08:09.029
I'll think about it.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.240
That's all we can ask.

08:11.616 --> 08:13.909
Wow, Drama,
you swore on your career?

08:13.994 --> 08:15.911
I had my balls crossed.

08:17.497 --> 08:21.709
The most important thing
is that you present a united front.

08:21.793 --> 08:24.753
This is what
we have decided is best for the family.

08:24.963 --> 08:27.673
- I didn't decide that.
- Ari, please,

08:27.757 --> 08:29.884
we need to make the kids feel okay about this.

08:29.968 --> 08:31.385
Well, I don't know how to do that.

08:31.469 --> 08:34.013
That's why we're here, to learn.

08:34.097 --> 08:35.722
Let's try a little role play.

08:35.807 --> 08:39.184
Melissa, you'll be Sarah.
Ari, talk to your daughter.

08:41.354 --> 08:42.520
Honey,

08:45.483 --> 08:49.820
I love your mother
and you guys more than anything,

08:50.614 --> 08:53.949
- but your mother has decided...
- Ari.

08:54.242 --> 08:56.452
Lies. We have decided...

08:56.536 --> 09:01.081
We have decided
that we are getting a divorce.

09:01.666 --> 09:02.708
Why?

09:02.792 --> 09:05.711
- I have no idea.
- Really? You have none?

09:05.795 --> 09:06.837
No.

09:11.801 --> 09:13.177
I would like to tell the kids tonight.

09:13.303 --> 09:14.887
- Can you do that?
- What is the rush?

09:14.971 --> 09:18.057
Are you trying to get a quickie
divorce so you can run off with Flay?

09:18.141 --> 09:20.684
- We broke up.
- Why?

09:20.769 --> 09:24.230
Because he knew
I wasn't ready for a relationship now,

09:24.314 --> 09:27.691
unlike you who have somehow in less than
a week managed to fall for a woman

09:27.776 --> 09:29.652
that I've long suspected you of being with.

09:29.736 --> 09:30.945
No. We ended it, too.

09:32.072 --> 09:33.113
Why?

09:33.198 --> 09:35.407
Because she knows that I still love you.

09:37.160 --> 09:39.328
- Do you still love him?
- What kind of question is that?

09:39.412 --> 09:42.331
- Of course I do.
- Well, maybe it's not too late to try again.

09:42.457 --> 09:46.543
My life is disappearing
and I don't wanna wake up and find myself 60

09:46.628 --> 09:49.588
- and have no one to talk to.
- You can always talk to me.

09:49.673 --> 09:52.091
- You don't listen to me.
- I'm... I'm listening right now.

09:52.175 --> 09:54.343
You have been an absentee
father and husband for years

09:54.427 --> 09:57.179
and I know you don't mean it,
but I don't want that anymore.

09:57.264 --> 10:00.557
Absentee father?
I resent what you're saying to me right now.

10:00.642 --> 10:02.059
And I don't think our kids would agree.

10:02.143 --> 10:04.687
- You can ask them.
- I will.

10:04.771 --> 10:07.273
And then we will tell them tonight?

10:08.483 --> 10:09.858
Yeah. Okay.

10:11.361 --> 10:13.946
You're gonna love her. Trust me.

10:14.030 --> 10:17.241
Ma, between this and E,
you might even get me back to New York.

10:17.325 --> 10:19.159
Really. Ma, I love you.

10:19.244 --> 10:21.287
I'll call you on the way. Bye.

10:21.371 --> 10:23.289
So you're really
gonna move back to New York?

10:23.373 --> 10:26.041
Well, Sophia is based out of there
and I can help E out

10:26.126 --> 10:28.585
and I know Johnny and Turtle will wanna
be there as much as possible.

10:28.670 --> 10:31.630
You guys are good friends.
I wouldn't move west of Gower for a dude.

10:31.715 --> 10:33.966
Well, we basically
lived together our whole lives.

10:34.050 --> 10:35.467
Hey, maybe y'all
will live together with the kid.

10:35.552 --> 10:38.137
- It'll be like 3 Men and a Little Lady.
- Yeah. And if he has a boy,

10:38.221 --> 10:40.264
it'll be like three men and two little men.

10:40.348 --> 10:41.682
Mr. Chase?

10:42.892 --> 10:44.893
What do you think of this?

10:44.978 --> 10:46.854
It's 5.4 carats.

10:47.522 --> 10:49.106
- Vince?
- Rachel.

10:49.190 --> 10:50.232
Hi.

10:50.984 --> 10:53.736
- How are you?
- Well, not as good as you obviously.

10:53.820 --> 10:56.155
- What's this about?
- I'm getting married.

10:56.239 --> 10:57.990
- Shut up.
- Really.

10:58.908 --> 11:00.826
